 Here is a JavaScript function that uses regex to extract a three character code from a filename in format "57-1Jn.usfm":

```javascript
function extractCode(filename) {
    var regex = /^(\d*)-(.*?)\.usfm$/; // Regular expression pattern to match the input string
    var match = filename.match(regex);  // Check if the string matches the given pattern

    if (match && match[2]) {  // If it is matched, return the three character code
        return match[2].slice(0, 3);
    } else {
        return null;   // Return null if no match is found
    }
}
```

You can use this function like so:

```javascript
var filename = "57-1Jn.usfm";
console.log(extractCode(filename));  // Outputs: "1Jn"
```
